%% RHOAI Build Config - Data Flow Diagram
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant Dev as Developer
    participant GH as GitHub<br/>rhoai-3.3 branch
    participant GHA as GitHub Actions<br/>Runner
    participant KA as RHOAI-Konflux-<br/>Automation
    participant Tekton as Konflux / Tekton<br/>Pipeline
    participant EC as Enterprise Contract<br/>Verification
    participant Quay as quay.io/rhoai<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant RRHI as registry.redhat.io<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant OLM as OLM<br/>Cluster

    Note over Dev,OLM: Flow 1: Operator Bundle Build (Konflux)
    Dev->>GH: Push to rhoai-3.3 branch
    GH->>Tekton: Webhook trigger<br/>TLS 1.2+, GitHub webhook secret
    Tekton->>Tekton: Build operator bundle image<br/>(bundle/, csv-patch, bundle-patch)
    Tekton->>Quay: Push odh-operator-bundle<br/>HTTPS/443, Konflux SA
    Tekton->>EC: Run Enterprise Contract task
    EC->>Quay: Verify image signatures<br/>HTTPS/443, cosign public key
    EC-->>Tekton: Verification result

    Note over Dev,OLM: Flow 2: Bundle Processing (GitHub Actions)
    Dev->>GH: Push to bundle/ or to-be-processed/
    GH->>GHA: Trigger workflow<br/>TLS 1.2+, GitHub token
    GHA->>KA: Fetch shared automation utils<br/>HTTPS/443, GitHub PAT
    KA-->>GHA: Automation scripts
    GHA->>GHA: Process bundle CSV<br/>Patch images, update refs
    GHA->>GH: Commit updated bundle<br/>HTTPS/443, GitHub token

    Note over Dev,OLM: Flow 3: Image Registry Mirroring (Disconnected)
    OLM->>RRHI: Pull operator images<br/>HTTPS/443, Pull secret
    Note right of OLM: ImageDigestMirrorSet<br/>redirects if disconnected
    OLM->>Quay: Mirror redirect (if configured)<br/>HTTPS/443, Pull secret

    Note over Dev,OLM: Flow 4: Operator Installation via OLM
    OLM->>OLM: Read FBC catalog fragment<br/>(v4.19/v4.20/v4.21)
    OLM->>RRHI: Pull operator bundle<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+
    OLM->>OLM: Deploy rhods-operator<br/>(3 replicas, webhook server)
    OLM->>OLM: Install CRDs (24 types)<br/>Register webhooks (9443/TCP)
